notesStmt.note: Title from title page of vol. 1 (f. 1r).
Description of the manuscript from the Martin Breslauer catalog on file in the Library.
The library of Rossi was actually sold during his lifetime to Bartolomeo Corsini and later became part of the Biblioteca Corsiniana in Rome.

msContents.summary: Contains the carefully compiled catalogs of 7,782 (falso 7.772) volumes of post-1500 printed books (f. 1-241 of vol. 1), with individual prices for all items and a total value of "scudi romani" 7,975.05; 1,307 incunable volumes (f. 242-290 of vol. 1), valued at sc. rom. 4,501.40; 415 manuscript codices, valued at sc. rom. 1,212.10. Each of the two volumes is notarized at the end.
